			<div class="row design-row">
				<div class="col-md-3">
					<img id="mountain-img" class="responsive left-block" src="https://yhwhapparel.files.wordpress.com/2017/04/mountain.png"/>
				</div>
				<div class="col-md-9">
					<h4> Mountains Baseball Cap </h4>
					<p> Mountains are often associated with sheer might--the idea that if only
					we had enough power, we could move huge obstacles. When we face trials
					that seem to exceed our strengths, let us instead surrender our
					inabilities at the feet of our Father, whose strength is made perfect
					in our weakness. From a distance, our daunting challenges seem unshakeable,
					but when we patiently put our trust in God and approach with His full confidence,
					we will begin to see how far He has moved our mountains. </p>
					<p> When we see this mountain, it should symbolize surrender, not
						personal strength or will. Though counterintuitive, the source of our
						strength is not within ourselves, but found and made stable in God. As
						Christians, we can rest assured in knowing that God will be moving the
						mountains for us--that it’s not about what we can do, but what He can
						do with the little faith that we offer up to Him. </p>
				</div>
